dcterms:creator: Nicolas Fiorini
David J. Lipman
Zhiyong Lu
dcterms:description: MEDLINE is a widely used source of biomedical literature articles, primarily consisting of titles, abstracts, and indexing terms (MeSH terms) as a surrogate for full text articles. It is openly accessible and searchable via PubMed.
dcterms:title: MEDLINE

dcterms:creator: Si Zheng
Ying Zhang
Ying Liu
dcterms:description: The Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) is a major biomedical knowledge base that enables semantic understanding and interoperability among different software applications by combining widely used dictionaries in the biomedical field.
dcterms:title: UMLS (Unified Medical Language System)

dcterms:creator: Balu Bhasuran
dcterms:description: Medical Subject Headings (MESH) is used for indexing and retrieval of PubMed articles, providing a structured vocabulary for biomedical concepts.
dcterms:title: MESH (Medical Subject Headings)

dcterms:creator: Halil Kilicoglu
D. Shin
M. Fiszman
G. Rosemblat
T. C. Rindflesch
dcterms:description: SemMedDB is a repository of semantic relations extracted from PubMed articles, containing predictions of subject-predicate-object triples.
dcterms:title: SemMedDB
